name: DESERT FALSE INDIGO
description: petioles two to five centimeters long; leaflets two to five centimeters long; yellow stamens extend beyond petals.
habitat: streamcourses at and near the base of the mountains.

name: BIG BLUESTEM
description: flower cluster three-parted, resembling an upside-down turkey foot.

name: CREEPING HOLLYGRAPE
common_name: Oregon grape, holly-grape, creeping oregon grape
description: above-ground stem short or lacking; leaflets broad with a few spiny teeth.

name: STINGING NETTLE
description: leaves opposite (in pairs) glabrous (hairless) on upper surface with stinging hairs on lower surface.
